attributes.Long form description: The student is assembling a piece of furniture with four legs and a flat top. The student begins by inspecting the furniture and grabbing an allen wrench. The student then aligns the first leg and screws it into tray. The student prepares to screw in the second leg, but first rotates the furniture regularly. The student then screws in the second leg, followed by the third and fourth. Finally, the student aligns the holes in the flat top table with the ones in the furniture legs and screws.

attributes.Transcription: Hello, welcome to our study, in front of you, you will see all the parts needed to assamble a nice stand from IKEA.
The task for now will be to please assemble it.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the first leg.

attributes.Transcription: Please take the shelf and place it on its long end with the bottom facing you.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should place the tray vertically on the table.

attributes.Transcription: Please place it vertically on the table. And screw the foot on the top left. Please use the metal holes in the foot. Then, please use the middle hole in the point.
And screw the foot on the top left

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should align with the middle hole.

attributes.Transcription: Pleas use the middle hole in the foot.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the second leg.

attributes.Transcription: Please rotate the shelf so that the foot you just assembled is on the bottom.  Please rotate once more such that it is on it's short side.

attributes.Action sentence: The student screws the third leg of the furniture.
The student assembles the fourth leg of the furniture.
The student assembles the flat top shelf.

attributes.Transcription: That includes everything in this task. You might press the stop button.
